title: recipes_Loosemeat_Sandwiches_II
text:
Title: Loosemeat Sandwiches II.
.
Description: Ground beef and chicken gumbo soup from a can -- quick and easy, serve it on a bun..
.
Ingredients:.
- 1 pound lean ground beef.
- 1 (10.75 ounce) can condensed chicken gumbo soup.
.
Instructions:.
- In large skillet over medium heat, cook ground beef until brown, 5 to 10 minutes. Drain. Return meat to skillet, with soup. Simmer until heated through, 5 minutes. Serve hot..
.
Nutrients:.
calories: 168 kcal.
carbohydrateContent: 3 g.
cholesterolContent: 51 mg.
fiberContent: 1 g.
proteinContent: 16 g.
saturatedFatContent: 4 g.
sodiumContent: 432 mg.
sugarContent: 1 g.
fatContent: 10 g.
unsaturatedFatContent: 0 g.
.
Serves: 6 servings.
